      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIGER'S GAMBIT (2) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.97) at Maitland behind More Drama in a Maiden. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Top chance in this line up. STREET JUSTICE (1) struggling to find form but drawn the rails here. Last time finished 4th over 388m at Gosford beaten 12 lengths (23.15) behind Hey Zipper in a Maiden on June 23. One of the better chances. DAKILA (8) was strongly fancied and drifted back but wound up hard to hit the frame, 3 lengths from the winner (22.85) at Gosford in Maiden. Well placed and gets her chance. CANYA SLAY (3) looks an each-way chance.",
